Leading Real Estate Development Company, Diyar Al Muharraq has announced the completion of infrastructure works that included the extension of water, rainwater, electricity, and sewage networks as well as the construction of access roads Diyar Al Muharraq Residential City in Bahrain. The works, which also included the extension of irrigation and telecommunications networks to Era Homes, Al Naseem, and Mozoon projects that are all within the Diyar Al Muharraq development, alongside future projects that will be in the area, were concluded last month. Also Read: North Manama Causeway Phase 2 and Busaiteen Link Project in Bahrain Complete The infrastructure development works especially for the roads in Diyar Al Muharraq Residential City were implemented in a total number of two phases. Paving and road lighting works were completed in the later phase and were delivered in six months. The junction that was present was converted and upgraded from a three-way to a four-way junction In addition, four roundabouts were added for the enhancement of road connectivity. The consultancy for the supervision and design of the project was under the expertise of AECOM. The Bahrain-based developer, Diyar Al Muharraq, revealed through a statement that the road works aforementioned were also implemented with current and future projects, throughout the entire city, in consideration. Moreover, Ahmed AL Ammadi, CEO Engineer to the company confidently expressed that the completion of the road works is an achievement for the company. He added that they always aim to better serve the residents and visitors of Diyar Al Muharraq through their current and future projects. He also stated that Diyar Al Muharraq is committed to the completion of projects promptly as well as the construction of high-quality infrastructure. He concluded his address by adding that the company is pleased to bear witness to the completion of one of the most fundamental components of the city.